Description:
Affordable Luxury, Position Perfect
Displaying all the quality & finesse, enjoy the easy life in contemporary style with this sensational townhome located to absolute perfection. Step inside onto stunning Tasmanian Oak flooring & discover gorgeous open-plan living & dining spaces, filled with natural light from the large windows overlooking the prized rear garden.
Impressive from start to finish, the home's smartly configured floorplan comprises 3 bedrooms (large master with walk-in robe & ensuite), sparkling family bathroom & guest powder room downstairs (3rd WC). Luxurious kitchen with stone-dressed benchtops, stainless appliances including gas cooktop, ample cupboard & bench space.
Entertaining outdoors will be a breeze with the homes private low-maintenance garden, boasting high-quality artificial grass, tranquil water feature, real-life vertical garden with irrigation & a double remote (semi-enclosed) garage. It is only upon your inspection outdoors you will truly appreciate what's on offer.
With additional benefits including ducted heating, split-system cooling, study nook, hardwood timber staircase, 40mm stone-benchtops throughout, floor-to-ceiling tiles in bathrooms, high square set ceilings, downlights throughout, video intercom & much much more!
Within close proximity wetlands/walking track, playgrounds, newly developed sports grounds, kindergarten, easy access Craigieburn Central, public transport & all other important amenities.
If space, quality & location are high on your agenda, then this home needs to be on your must-see list!

Description:
A Real Beauty for the Tradies, with Massive Shedding
Adjoining a park reserve, on a 660m2 block, in a lovely quiet location, this gorgeous well built solid brick, double storey 4 bedroom plus study home oozes charm and appeal with its olde world style and offers someone an abundance of shedding, making it ideal for a tradie, someone with a boat and/or caravan or a small truck.
Off the lovely formal entry, the home features a cosy formal lounge room with timber floors and a wood heater that also flows through to the bright dining area. The fresh and bright kitchen with a dishwasher looks out onto the big backyard and the fenced in ground pool, gazebo and paved verandah. Also downstairs is a large bedroom with robes, the large laundry and a WC.
Upstairs, you will find the enormous master bedroom which could also be used as another living area for the kids to enjoy with a separate study or retreat adjoining, and also opens out onto the balcony that offers views through to the Dandenongs. There are also another 2 double bedrooms with robes and a gorgeous fully tiled bathroom plus another separate WC to service upstairs.
Letâs not forget the ducted heating throughout, the massive shedding that includes a high clearance open garage (9m x 6.5m x 3.2m), the double remote garage (9m x 6m) converted to a man cave for the boys, with wood heating and a bar and finally all the extra driveway parking.
All of this is in close proximity to Woolworths, cafes, take away foods, Bunnings, train stations, buses, parks, sporting grounds, Schools and Kindergartens and only a 5 minute drive to the Cranbourne Park Shopping Centre and finally, within easy access to both the City and Bays.
A gorgeous home that offers plenty, come see for yourself.

Description:
STUNNING HOME WITH BEAUTIFUL BONES
CRANBOURNE CENTRAL - Nestled in a quiet spot in Cranbourne sits 11 Baystone Drive. This property would make a great investment to add to your portfolio or the perfect home to put a bit of love into to make it shine.
From the entry of the home you are greeted with a cheerful, sunny sunken living area which has an abundance of space, ready to be turned into a formal living area or whatever you'd like it to be (it's the perfect opportunity to secure your own pool table finally!).
Continuing on down the hallway, the kitchen overlooks an equally as bright meals area and has the space for a dream kitchen to be made. Featuring a gas cooktop, dishwasher, overhead cupboards and plenty of bench space, there is room for the whole family to get involved in making dinner.
You will find 2 good sized bedrooms in this home. The master features a full length mirrored robe, full ensuite and is amazingly spacious. The additional bedroom is also very well sized and benefits from built in robes.
The property features a laundry room with rear access, spacious main bathroom with a separate shower, spa bath and separate toilet.
Stepping outside you will be greeted with a decked entertainment area, which overlooks the lush green garden. The large block of 661m2 means that there is plenty of room to enjoy, creating a peaceful environment for the family.
The property also features a double car garage with rear access, perfect for if you have any toys which need storing.
Features include:
- Large 661m2 block
- Ducted heating
- Two large living areas with separate dining
- Master with ensuite
- Double car garage with rear access
Located in the Sladen Park Estate, this property benefits from being in the central area of Cranbourne, one of the most established and sought after areas. With a mix of older homes on larger blocks and units. Located within walking distance to all facilities, including the newly renovated Cranbourne Park, a range of restaurants, Cranbourne Secondary College and Cranbourne Train Station. Cranbourne Central provides the perfect combination for any resident.
At Ray White Cranbourne our price indications are based upon probable market value, the likely selling price and vendor expectations. You can view with confidence that vendors will sell within the range with favourable conditions.

TWO separate living areas to enjoy a formal lounge upon entry and an open plan family room at the rear

HUGE enclosed alfresco - perfect for entertaining all year round plus spacious backyard with plenty of space for kids and pets to play
Double lock up garage with internal access and rear roller door for extra secure parking for a caravan or trailer
Extras include: Ducted heating, split system air-conditioning, coonara fireplace, roller shutters to some windows, downlights throughout, garden shed for storage and MUCH more!
To top it off the location is conveniently central to everything you could ever need! APPOINTMENTS TO INSPECT NOT AVAILABLE UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE.
This incredible home is PACKED with features and will surely tick all the boxes! Highlights include TWO living areas to enjoy, an outdoor alfresco all your friends will be envious of and to top it off double side access for those who need to store a caravan, boat or trailer. Found in the popular and established Brookland Greens Estate at the end of a quiet court ensures peaceful living and all amenities at your fingertips.
Main features include:
Spacious Master suite complete with walk in robe and en-suite.
Three further bedrooms all serviced by built in robes
TWO living areas to enjoy a formal lounge as you walk into the home and an open plan family room at the rear
Central kitchen complete with stainless steel appliances, dishwasher, breakfast bar and plenty of bench and cupboard space
Family bathroom with separate toilet
HUGE outdoor entertaining area with built in BBQ and chimenea fireplace perfect for entertaining all year round
Great sized backyard for kids and pets to play

Ideally located in a peaceful and quite location in the highly desirable Brookland Greens Estate, this family-friendly neighbourhood offers a lot of opportunity and great amenities. Only a few blocks away is the Brookland Greens Reserve featuring a children's playground and plenty of space to kick the footy. The new Cranbourne West Shopping complex is also only a short drive away offering a supermarket as well as other specialty stores. Transport is a breeze being a short distance to the M1 and Cranbourne Train Station and there are multiple schools in proximity for all your schooling needs.

Description:
Living Large on the Park
With 24 squares of living area, this near new, low maintenance townhouse, does not compromise on space.
As such, it would be an ideal first home, a home for a young family, or a downsize opportunity.
The townhouse is located in Cranbourne, within easy access to the South Gippsland Hwy/M1. It is situated within a very peaceful part of the suburb. There is a park directly in front of the residence, which would be ideal for residents who want to conveniently get out and unwind. However, it still has the convenience of being close to amenities such as the Amstel Club, Ranfurlie Golf Course, St Peter's College, childcare facilities and the Woolworths shopping precinct on the corner of Hall Rd & Evans Rd (due to open over the coming months).
The property boasts a unique 32m2 studio space above the garage. This space would suit a range of purposes including a fourth bedroom, dedicated work space, or retreat for teens or parents. Plumbing is already within the wall cavities of this space, meaning it could be converted into a fully self-contained area with a minimum of fuss or expense.
The town house is currently leased to an ideal tenant who has expressed the possibility of staying should an investor purchase. Also available with vacant possession.
Features include:
- 3 main bedrooms, master bedroom with full en-suite and walk in robe, bedrooms 2 & 3 with BIR's
- Huge 4th bedroom/studio or (possible teenagers retreat) above the double garage
- Impressive kitchen with stone bench tops and stainless steel appliances including dishwasher
- 5kw split system in lounge (cooling/heating)
- ducted heating throughout
- Open plan living areas leading to the rear courtyard
- Powder room and separate laundry downstairs
- Family bathroom with a large shower
- balcony to master bedroom
- double garage with rear roller door to yard
- solar hot water system
For more information about this residence please call Steve Pinirou on 0402 837 853 at Eview Group - Bayside.

Description:
Approved Plans and Permits for a 2nd Dwelling
Literally so central to everything, in a court location, this 2 bedroom home currently tenanted, has approved plans and permits to build a second dwelling at the rear, with the initial building works already commenced and underway and all the waiting for permit approvals done.
The current owner has already paid for the 2 lot subdivision, endorsed plans and the building permit, has approval from South East Water, cleared the building area, soil test, and has already installed the initial plumbing, all of this can be a time sponge, when trying to commence a building project.
The home itself has a formal lounge with a wood heater, air conditioner and timber floors, which are throughout most of the home, kitchen has gas cooking and there are two large bedrooms each with sliding robes. The tenant has been there approximately 4 years, and would like to stay.
The home is walking distance to the train station, Coles, shops, parks, schools and even McDonalds, a fantastic location.
The home is a fantastic opportunity for Builders, Developers and Investors, come see for yourself.

Description:
**SOLD BY PAUL RINGERI**
CRANBOURNE CENTRAL: Superbly situated at the rear of a quiet complex of only 3 units with ample visitor parking, this sensational prospect is located in close proximity to schools, parks and major shopping facilities. 3/44 Stawell Street is a beautifully presented 2 bedroom unit that pairs contemporary comfort with the ultimate in lifestyle convenience.
An exciting opportunity to break into the market or downsize in style, this single level residence impresses with bright open plan living and dining areas complete with low maintenance timber and tiled flooring. The modernised hostess kitchen with breakfast bar is a major selling point and boasts stainless steel appliances including a gas cooktop.
Step outside and be greeted by a generous entertainment space with room for a large outdoor setting. The private terrace garden provides a serene place to relax and unwind at the end of a hard day's work or why not fire up the barbecue on weekends and dine alfresco style!
With a long list of recent upgrades the 2 very comfortable bedrooms have built-in robes and easy access to a sleek modern bathroom with freestanding rectangular tub and separate toilet. Added extras include RC/SS air-conditioning, ceiling fans, dishwasher and a single lock up garage.
If you believe in the age old theory that good real estate revolves around a central location then you won't be disappointed. Within moments to local primary/secondary schools and Chisholm TAFE together with South Gippsland Highway and Narre Warren-Cranbourne Road en route to the shopping facilities at Thompsons Parkway, Casey Central, the Hunt Club Village and Cranbourne Park shopping centre. Those that don't drive can take advantage of the public transport leading to the main street and, most importantly, the Cranbourne train station!
This is the perfect opportunity to break into the real estate market without breaking the bank ..... so don't delay!

If you believe in the age-old theory that good real estate revolves around a central location then you won't be disappointed. - All bedrooms with BIR's and reasonable in size.

This is not one to go past, with genuine sellers and an even more genuine price be sure not to miss out on this great opportunity! For all enquiries please Call Jason Brown Direct. 0423 768 424
